window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Forced out of the <i>Los Angeles Times</i> amid the latest budget cuts, newspaperman Jack McEvoy decides to go out with a bang, using his final days at the paper to write the definitive murder story of his career. He focuses on Alonzo Winslow, a 16-year-old drug dealer in jail after confessing to a brutal murder. But as he delves into the story, Jack realizes that Winslow's so-called confession is bogus. The kid might actually be innocent.</p> <p>Jack is soon running with his biggest story since <i>The Poetmade</i> his career years ago. He is tracking a killer who operates completely below police radar - and with perfect knowledge of any move against him. Including Jack's.&nbsp;</p>"; 
